      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Wash, then add the <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool, then squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can and chop it roughly</p><p>Trim, then finely slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
